comments: Maxey (PHI) moves laterally into White's (CHI) body after his gather, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Maxey (PHI) and Caruso (CHI) come together off-ball and the contact is marginal.
Maxey (PHI) holds his arms out slightly as he releases away from Caruso (CHI) and the contact away from the ball is marginal.

Caruso (CHI) moves alongside Maxey's (PHI) path and absorbs the marginal contact as Maxey leans in during the driving shot attempt. Williams (CHI) reaches in and initiates contact with Maxey's arm, which affects his driving shot attempt. The shooting foul should have been given to Williams.
White (CHI) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
Vucevic (CHI) moves alongside Embiid's (PHI) path and loses his balance on his own volition and falls to the ground. The contact during the layup attempt is marginal.
White (CHI) firms up in Embiid's (PHI) path and Embiid slips the marginal contact with the defender during the layup attempt at the basket.
Melton (PHI) brings his hand toward the ball and marginal lower body contact occurs with White (CHI) during the drive into the frontcourt.
Oubre Jr. (PHI) brings his right hand to the ball and deflects it away from White (CHI) during his dribble. The lower body contact after the deflection is considered incidental.
Caruso (CHI) makes contact with Oubre Jr.'s (PHI) left arm, which impacts his layup attempt at the basket.
Maxey (PHI) contests to DeRozan's (CHI) side and marginal lower body contact occurs with DeRozan's partially extended right leg.
Embiid (PHI) rests and removes his hand from Caruso's (CHI) side as he releases away during the pick and the contact is marginal.
Caruso (CHI) legally contests Maxey's (PHI) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.

Replay review of the foul called on Harris (PHI) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Harris is drawn into the air and turns his body toward DeRozan's (CHI) space as DeRozan steps toward the basket and begins his upward shooting motion. The ensuing contact with DeRozan's right arm affects the jump shot attempt.
White (CHI) jumps vertically and avoids making contact with Embiid (PHI) during the shot attempt in the paint. Embiid loses control of the ball on his own volition during his upward shooting motion.
Maxey (PHI) commits a take foul on DeRozan (CHI). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Harris (PHI) inbounds the ball within five seconds of receiving it from the game official.
Embiid (PHI) firms up in DeRozan's (CHI) path and his left arm brushes DeRozan's back during the screen and the contact is marginal.
Williams (CHI) moves alongside Embiid's (PHI) path and absorbs the marginal contact at the start of the drive.
